9
00:00:45,666 --> 00:00:48,499
Everyone gives meaning to a message in there 
own unique way

10
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:50,400
This idea was hardly new.

11
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:54,300
Scientists had studied the phenomenon of 
polysemic messages for a long time. 

12
00:00:54,300 --> 00:00:59,333
Polysemic meaning exactly that, different 
people interpreting a message in a different way.  

13
00:00:59,333 --> 00:01:03,333
According to these scientists each act of 
communication relies

14
00:01:03,333 --> 00:01:07,366
on a communication system, without which we 
wouldn't understand each other.  

15
00:01:07,366 --> 00:01:10,899
The study of these systems iscalled semiotics or semiology,

16
00:01:10,900 --> 00:01:13,433
the so called study of âsignsâ and âsignificationâ.

17
00:01:13,433 --> 00:01:16,666
A sign is basically everything that 
communicates something. 

18
00:01:16,666 --> 00:01:19,866
A spoken word, a gesture, a glance, a photo, a 
cartoon,

19
00:01:19,866 --> 00:01:23,366
a written sentence, a hieroglyph, they are all 
signs. 

20
00:01:23,366 --> 00:01:27,366
The process of giving meaning to these signs is 
called signification. 

21
00:01:27,366 --> 00:01:31,766
Without going to deep into this fascinating topic, 
