22
00:01:31,766 --> 00:01:35,232
the influence of semiotic theories on mass 
communication theory. 

23
00:01:35,233 --> 00:01:40,633
This approach views communication not as a 
linear process but as an exchange of meaning.

24
00:01:40,633 --> 00:01:46,299
The sender puts meaning in a message and the 
receiver takes meaning from a message.

25
00:01:46,300 --> 00:01:48,500
Under influence of semiotic theories,

26
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:51,766
communication scientists became more 
interested in the reception of a message

27
00:01:51,766 --> 00:01:56,399
and acknowledged that communication can 
indeed have multiple valid outcomes.  

28
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:58,966
