29
00:01:58,966 --> 00:02:02,232
proposed by linguist Roman Jacobson in 1960.

30
00:02:02,233 --> 00:02:06,233
He starts with familiar elements from Shannon 
and Weavers transmission model: 

31
00:02:06,233 --> 00:02:10,233
An addresser sends a message to an 
addressee using a channel. 

32
00:02:10,233 --> 00:02:12,799
He added to the model elements from semiotics   

33
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:16,500
Like the idea that every message refers to 
something outside of the message,

34
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:18,466
which he called context. 

35
00:02:18,466 --> 00:02:22,932
Also, the specific form that our communication 
takes, for instance a written word,

36
00:02:22,933 --> 00:02:27,466
 made up of letters, is called a code.  

37
00:02:27,466 --> 00:02:30,132
Successful communication, according to 
Jacobson,

38
00:02:30,133 --> 00:02:33,933
can only exist when all of these elements are in 
place. 

39
00:02:33,933 --> 00:02:37,433
Also, each act of communication has one 
dominant function

40
00:02:37,433 --> 00:02:42,066
that relates to one of these elements in this 
model. 

41
00:02:42,066 --> 00:02:46,899
Let's review these functions that Jacobson 
identified. 

42
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:49,900
When the primary purpose of a message is to 
communicate

43
00:02:49,900 --> 00:02:54,633
the emotions and attitudes of a sender, this is 
called the emotive function. 

44
00:02:54,633 --> 00:02:57,533
For instance when I write a love letter to my 
girlfriend.

45
00:02:57,533 --> 00:02:59,733
The second function is conative. 

46
00:02:59,733 --> 00:03:02,833
If a receiver is directly addressed to do 
something specific.

47
00:03:02,833 --> 00:03:07,766
An example is a commercial that tells us to 
âbuy this flavour of ice cream!â. 

48
00:03:07,766 --> 00:03:11,499
The referential or descriptive function 
corresponds with the context 

49
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:15,200
and happens when a message primarily 
describes a situation.

50
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:18,533
Perhaps a news report is a good example for 
this. 

51
00:03:18,533 --> 00:03:22,299
Sometimes the main purpose of communicating 
is to keep the lines open, 

52
00:03:22,300 --> 00:03:25,300
when we have coffee each week with a friend for 
instance. 

53
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:29,000
This is called a phatic function and relates to the 
channel. 

54
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:32,600
A poetic function means that the message is an 
end in itself,

55
00:03:32,600 --> 00:03:38,266
a painting for example that aims at being a 
beautiful and aesthetically pleasing piece of art.

56
00:03:38,266 --> 00:03:41,299
And finally there is the metalingual function,

57
00:03:41,300 --> 00:03:44,200
when we use communication to explain the 
codes that we use. 

58
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:46,233
For instance a dictionary. 

